cp - cp stands for Copy. This command is used to copy a file.
Syntax - cp <existing file> <new file>

Following are the commands related to cp which are as follows :-

1) To copy directoy with its sub-directories :
   Syntax - cp -r
   
2) To copy multiple files or directories in a directory :
   Syntax - cp file1 file2 file3 directory_name
   
3) To backup the existing file before overwriting it :
   Syntax - cp -backup
   
4) To create hard link file :
   Syntax - cp -l
   
5) To preserve attribute of a file :
   Syntax - cp -p
 
